Since I suggested it, I should probably write why:

The thought is that the version is like a checksum, we don't care about the format or anything about it, only if it's changed or not. When a the version is changed, it will remove the old one, and add in this (like overwrite). This is similar to overwrite, but with one big difference, I don't have to think about the last version used. With overwrite, you need to remember if you have to overwrite, this can cause subtle bugs when forgotten. A better name for it would probably be something like `id` or `hash`. I think this can actually replace overwrite, since you can just change the version to get the same effect.

