@peol I don't see the issue. Does it really matter if the cached asset is dropped to early? It will just be refetched from the server. You can't rely on it being in localStorage anyway. What if the user wipes it themselves?

The nice thing about the automatic trasher is that it will allow for new entries to take priority instead of old (and maybe even obsolete) entries. An even better use case is if the user doesn't use TTL. Then the asset would live in localStorage forever, and block new entries, but with the automatic space saving, it would be trashed when the space was needed (we would add a timeStamp on when every entry was added to localStorage).

